## 10. Chapter Finale — Twinkle, Varied and Phrased

Here is the finale program for this chapter: **Twinkle Twinkle, with three variations**. Each time through, we vary the melody in a different way:

1. **Original** — as written, middle register.
2. **Octave up** — same melody, transposed +12 semitones.
3. **Descending sequence** — the first motif repeated three times, each a whole step lower.
4. **Velocity accent** — the second phrase with alternating loud/soft notes.

```scheme
(define (pitch->number p)
  (case p
    ((C4) 60)  ((D4) 62)  ((E4) 64)  ((F4) 65)
    ((G4) 67)  ((A4) 69)  ((B4) 71)
    ((C5) 72)  ((D5) 74)  ((E5) 76)  ((F5) 77)
    ((G5) 79)  ((A5) 81)  ((B5) 83)
    (else 60)))

(define (number->pitch n)
  (case n
    ((60) 'C4)  ((62) 'D4)  ((64) 'E4)  ((65) 'F4)
    ((67) 'G4)  ((69) 'A4)  ((71) 'B4)
    ((72) 'C5)  ((74) 'D5)  ((76) 'E5)  ((77) 'F5)
    ((79) 'G5)  ((81) 'A5)  ((83) 'B5)
    (else 'C4)))

(define (transpose-motif motif semitones)
  (map
    (lambda (n)
      (let ((old-pitch (first n))
            (dur (second n))
            (vel (third n)))
        (let ((new-pitch (number->pitch (+ (pitch->number old-pitch) semitones))))
          (list new-pitch dur vel))))
    motif))

(define (play-motif motif)
  (for-each
    (lambda (n)
      (note (first n) (second n) (third n)))
    motif))

(define phrase-1
  (list
    (list 'C4 'quarter 80)
    (list 'C4 'quarter 80)
    (list 'G4 'quarter 80)
    (list 'G4 'quarter 80)
    (list 'A4 'quarter 80)
    (list 'A4 'quarter 80)
    (list 'G4 'half 80)))

(define phrase-2
  (list
    (list 'G4 'quarter 80)
    (list 'F4 'quarter 80)
    (list 'F4 'quarter 80)
    (list 'E4 'quarter 80)
    (list 'E4 'quarter 80)
    (list 'D4 'quarter 80)
    (list 'D4 'quarter 80)
    (list 'C4 'half 80)))

(define (vary-velocity motif pattern)
  (map
    (lambda (n vel)
      (list (first n) (second n) vel))
    motif
    pattern))

;; Variation 1: Original
(play-motif phrase-1)
(play-motif phrase-2)

;; Variation 2: Octave up
(play-motif (transpose-motif phrase-1 12))
(play-motif (transpose-motif phrase-2 12))

;; Variation 3: Descending sequence of first motif
(define first-motif (list (list 'C4 'quarter 80) (list 'C4 'quarter 80)))
(play-motif first-motif)
(play-motif (transpose-motif first-motif -2))
(play-motif (transpose-motif first-motif -4))

;; Variation 4: Phrase 2 with alternating loud/soft
(define phrase-2-accented
  (vary-velocity phrase-2 '(100 60 100 60 100 60 100 80)))
(play-motif phrase-2-accented)
```

<!-- BUILD: chapter 4 finale — Twinkle with four variations (original, octave-up, descending sequence, velocity accent) -->

You hear the tune four times, each iteration exploring a different dimension of variation: pitch register, sequential transposition, and dynamic accent. The melody is the same, but the *character* shifts each time.

[VISUAL: Four-staff score showing the four variations side-by-side, labeled \"Var. 1 (original)\", \"Var. 2 (8va)\", \"Var. 3 (sequence)\", \"Var. 4 (accented)\", with note-sprites decorating the staves]

