### 21. Phrasing with Rests—The Breath

**Rests** create *silence*—the breath between phrases. Let's phrase Twinkle with deliberate rests:

```scheme
;; Twinkle with rests between phrases
(define (twinkle-phrased-with-rests)
  (note/strike 'C4 'quarter 0.8)
  (note/strike 'C4 'quarter 0.8)
  (note/strike 'G4 'quarter 0.8)
  (note/strike 'G4 'quarter 0.8)
  (note/strike 'rest 'quarter 0.0)  ;; breath
  (note/strike 'A4 'quarter 0.8)
  (note/strike 'A4 'quarter 0.8)
  (note/strike 'G4 'half 0.8)
  (note/strike 'rest 'quarter 0.0))  ;; breath

(twinkle-phrased-with-rests)
```

`[VISUAL: Staff showing Twinkle with quarter rests between phrases; rest sprites (quarter-rest glyphs) are visible and still.]`

<!-- BUILD: render the phrased-with-rests staff; rest sprites are still (no bop); on press, sound the melody with silences -->

The rests let the melody *breathe*. Without them, the melody runs together; with them, each phrase has space to land.

