### 31. A Modal Melody—Dorian Mode

A **mode** is a scale with a different pattern of whole and half steps. The **Dorian mode** on D is **D E F G A B C D**—like D natural minor, but with a raised 6th (B instead of Bb). Let's write a Dorian melody:

```scheme
;; Dorian melody on D (D E F G A B C D)
(define (dorian-melody)
  (note/strike 'D4 'quarter 0.8)
  (note/strike 'E4 'quarter 0.8)
  (note/strike 'F4 'quarter 0.8)
  (note/strike 'G4 'quarter 0.8)
  (note/strike 'A4 'quarter 0.8)
  (note/strike 'B4 'quarter 0.8)  ;; raised 6th (not Bb)
  (note/strike 'C5 'quarter 0.8)
  (note/strike 'D5 'half 0.8))

(dorian-melody)
```

`[VISUAL: Staff showing the D Dorian melody with a natural sign on B (no flat).]`

<!-- BUILD: render the Dorian-melody staff; on press, sound the melody -->

Dorian mode sounds *folk-like* and *jazzy*—brighter than natural minor, darker than major.

